 Ngcobo - A 62-year-old woman is expected in court after she was arrested by Ngcobo police for alleged possesssion of dagga. "Vispol members quickly responded on information when they were busy patrolling around the area," said police spokesperon, Capt Namhla Mdleleni. "They conducted search and found plastic bags of dagga to the value of R3 000." She said that the 62-year-old woman was arrested and will appear before the Ngcobo Magistrate's Court on Tuesday facing charge of possession of dagga. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 